  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.8.6\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nI want to see an official hardware requirements document to have a full node in a machine.\r\n(I think that requirements will be different if someone wants a full or a light node).\r\nI would be useful if this document contains:\r\n- CPU\r\n- RAM\r\n- IOPS\r\n- Network\r\n- Disk space\r\n- Geth execution parameters for each type of hardware configuration.\r\n- Is it compatible with a cloud environment? (AWS/Azure/Google...)\r\n- Specific configurations for each clould enviornment\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n**There is no official documentation about different hardware configurations** (I haven't seen it). I have to ask for it in geth forums.\r\nFor this reason, I don't know if a slow sync is because a bad hardware configuration or a real Geth bug.\r\n\r\n",
